# Shell scripts MUST stay LF on every checkout. With core.autocrlf=true (this repo's
# Windows default), git would otherwise rewrite them to CRLF on checkout, and a CR in
# the shebang (`#!/usr/bin/env bash\r`) makes Git Bash fail with "No such file or
# directory" / "bad interpreter". This protects build scripts AND .claude hooks across
# both PCs. (Added after the 2026-05-29 hooks-launcher fix surfaced the CRLF risk.)
*.sh text eol=lf

# Windows batch files are CRLF.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
